#
# Install
#

# Required libraries : lua,
# Optional (but recommended) : mpi and netcdf

# Required includes : ops, seldon, talos
# Make symbolic links to the path of each required include in the include directory.

#
# Compilation
#

# Python interface
scons swig

# Your program.cpp
scons program

# By default it compiles with MPI and NetCDF support.
# To compile with MPI or/and without NetCDF, add options:
scons swig mpi=no netcdf=no
# The default is yes for both options.
 
#
# Install
#


# Only python interface need to be installed.
# Go into one directory of your PYTHONPATH and make symbolic links
# to the coefficient_repartition/python directory. If, for example,
# $HOME/lib is in your PYTHONPATH :
cd $HOME/lib
ln -s absolute/path/to/coefficient_repartition/python coefficient_repartition
ln -s absolute/path/to/coefficient_repartition/python coefficient_repartition_mpi


#
# Run
#


# To run python interface, in interactive python or in your script.py
# add this import line:
import coefficient_repartition as cr
# or
import coefficient_repartition_mpi as cr
# if you want MPI support.

# Refer to example directory for further details.